<div id="content" lang="en" dir="ltr">
<strong><a href="./MayLith">MayLith</a></strong>: I don't know how many countless times I've seen this without noticing it! You're in the game, you hit "=" to enter the options sheet. The first string at the top of the screen is "Angband options". It should be "ToME options". <p>
<a href="./MassimilianoMarangio">MassimilianoMarangio</a>: "ToME options" is also used for some additional options not used in Angband (point (5) in the options screen). 
</p>
<p>
<strong><a href="./NeilStevens">NeilStevens</a></strong>: I don't think the distinctions make any sense, but the options are being revised in ToME 3 anyway. 
</p>
<p>
<strong><a href="./MayLith">MayLith</a></strong>: *shrug* From what I understood, you wanted to get rid of references to Angband in the game, which is why I reported it. Anyway, I guess it's irrelevant if it's changing in 3. 
</p>
<p>
<strong><a href="./NeilStevens">NeilStevens</a></strong>: I agree with you!  I said the distinction between "Angband" and "ToME" options doesn't make sense! 
</p>
<p>
<strong><a href="./MayLith">MayLith</a></strong>: *quizzical look* *stares at the screen* *stares at the screen again* What I had read was that it didn't make any sense to bother distinguishing between Angband and ToME....which itself made no sense to me. <img src="./wiki/classic/img/smile.png" alt=":)" height="15" width="15"> I need a vacation.... 
</p>
<p>
<a href="./MassimilianoMarangio">MassimilianoMarangio</a>: What about a more generic first line, like "Game options", "Option sets" or simply "Options" ? 
</p>
